e">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/fda-approved-at-home-brain-stimulation-device-aims-to-treat-depression-by-changing-patients-brain-excitability-180988654/</guid></item><item><title>巨大的海狮将人群吸引到旧金山著名的 39 号码头。然后，一个新的矮胖的表演者窃取了他的身份</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/chonkers-the-massive-sea-lion-drew-crowds-to-san-franciscos-famed-pier-39-then-a-new-chunky-showstopper-stole-his-identity-180988691/</link><description>北海狮是码头上的不寻常访客，码头上通常栖息着较小的加州海狮。然而，他可能在几天前​​就已经搬走了，在此期间，该地区较常见物种的一个巨大成员欺骗了旁观者</description><pubDate>Thu, 07 May 2026 16:19:46 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/chonkers-the-massive-sea-lion-drew-crowds-to-san-franciscos-famed-pier-39-then-a-new-chunky-showstopper-stole-his-identity-180988691/</guid></item><item><title>城市鸟类似乎比男性更害怕女性——科学家们不知道为什么</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/urban-birds-seem-to-be-more-fearful-of-women-than-men-and-scientists-dont-know-why-180988688/</link><description>该研究调查了五个欧洲国家城市中的 37 种鸟类。在飞走之前，这些动物平均允许男性比女性靠近约三英尺</description><pubDate>Thu, 07 May 2026 14:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/urban-birds-seem-to-be-more-fearful-of-women-than-men-and-scientists-dont-know-why-180988688/</guid></item><item><title>在成为国父之前，本杰明·富兰克林创立了借阅图书馆。现在，他的物品在拍卖前陈列在那里</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/before-benjamin-franklins-belongings-head-to-auction-they-go-on-display-at-a-place-he-loved-and-invented-a-library-in-philadelphia-180988692/</link><description>1731 年，书籍爱好者富兰克林创建了费城图书馆公司，本周游客可以在这里看到他收藏的论文，价值估计为 300 万至 450 万美元</description><pubDate>Thu, 07 May 2026 13:43:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/before-benjamin-franklins-belongings-head-to-auction-they-go-on-display-at-a-place-he-loved-and-invented-a-library-in-philadelphia-180988692/</guid></item><item><title>这是水下机器人在法国最深的沉船中发现的东西，这是一艘停泊在地中海底部的 16 世纪商船</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/heres-what-underwater-robots-are-finding-at-frances-deepest-shipwreck-a-16th-century-merchant-vessel-resting-at-the-bottom-of-the-mediterranean-180988685/</link><description>这艘船被称为“卡马拉特 4 号”，船上装载着大炮、大锅和数百件陶瓷——这些物品在海底仍然清晰可见。研究人员正在勘察该地点并仔细恢复一小部分文物</description><pubDate>Thu, 07 May 2026 10:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/heres-what-underwater-robots-are-finding-at-frances-deepest-shipwreck-a-16th-century-merchant-vessel-resting-at-the-bottom-of-the-mediterranean-180988685/</guid></item><item><title>二战后，这位德国艺术家通过颠倒了他的画作，彻底颠覆了艺术世界</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/after-world-war-ii-this-german-artist-turned-the-art-world-upside-down-literally-by-inverting-his-paintings-180988689/</link><description>乔治·巴塞利兹 (Georg Baselitz) 是一位擅长运用透视法并在头上翻转画布的著名画家，最近去世，享年 88 岁</description><pubDate>Wed, 06 May 2026 19:42:26 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/after-world-war-ii-this-german-artist-turned-the-art-world-upside-down-literally-by-inverting-his-paintings-180988689/</guid></item><item><title>澳大利亚能成为第一个消除宫颈癌的国家吗？进展顺利，但 HPV 疫苗接种率和筛查率正在下降</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/could-australia-be-the-first-country-to-eliminate-cervical-cancer-its-on-track-but-hpv-vaccination-and-screening-rates-are-falling-180988681/</link><description>该国于2007年实施了全国疫苗接种计划，以预防该疾病。新数据显示，2021年，没有25岁以下女性被诊断出患有宫颈癌，这是一个重要的里程碑</description><pubDate>Wed, 06 May 2026 15:57:33 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/could-australia-be-the-first-country-to-eliminate-cervical-cancer-its-on-track-but-hpv-vaccination-and-screening-rates-are-falling-180988681/</guid></item><item><title>《蝇王》在新迷你剧中首次出现在电视上。在 20 世纪 50 年代，现在著名的小说几乎从未出版过</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/new-miniseries-brings-lord-of-the-flies-to-television-for-the-first-time-in-the-1950s-the-now-famous-novel-almost-never-got-published-180988684/</link><description>出版商多次拒绝《蝇王》的原稿，但这个故事至今仍引起热议。作家威廉·戈尔丁后来荣获诺贝尔文学奖</description><pubDate>Wed, 06 May 2026 14:07:48 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/new-miniseries-brings-lord-of-the-flies-to-television-for-the-first-time-in-the-1950s-the-now-famous-novel-almost-never-got-published-180988684/</guid></item><item><title>鲸鱼蒂米在德国海岸搁浅数周后被释放到北海。这是正确的决定吗？</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/timmy-the-whale-was-released-into-the-sea-after-being-stranded-off-the-german-coast-for-weeks-was-that-the-right-call-180988679/</link><description>座头鲸于三月底首次进入浅水区，但过去几周其健康状况恶化。专家批评了拯救这只动物的努力，这可能弊大于利</description><pubDate>Wed, 06 May 2026 13:13:56 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/timmy-the-whale-was-released-into-the-sea-after-being-stranded-off-the-german-coast-for-weeks-was-that-the-right-call-180988679/</guid></item><item><title>汉坦病毒的致命爆发导致大西洋上的一艘游轮搁浅。以下是关于罕见传染病的知识</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-deadly-outbreak-of-hantavirus-has-stranded-a-cruise-ship-in-the-atlantic-ocean-heres-what-to-know-about-the-rare-contagion-180988680/</link><description>与该船有关的三人已死亡，卫生官员已确认共有两例确诊病例和五例疑似感染病例。该病毒通常通过受污染的啮齿动物粪便传播</description><pubDate>Tue, 05 May 2026 21:08:42 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-deadly-outbreak-of-hantavirus-has-stranded-a-cruise-ship-in-the-atlantic-ocean-heres-what-to-know-about-the-rare-contagion-180988680/</guid></item><item><title>面部识别找到了丢失的安妮·博林肖像吗？学者们争论人工智能是否解决了艺术史之谜还是仅仅混淆了艺术史之谜</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/did-facial-recognition-find-a-lost-portrait-of-anne-boleyn-scholars-debate-whether-ai-solved-or-merely-muddled-an-art-history-mystery-180988677/</link><description>亨利八世的第二任妻子被指控叛国，失去了理智。现在，一些研究人员认为，在皇家艺术收藏中的数十幅可能贴错标签的肖像画中，她也丢了脸。</description><pubDate>Tue, 05 May 2026 20:36:40 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/did-facial-recognition-find-a-lost-portrait-of-anne-boleyn-scholars-debate-whether-ai-solved-or-merely-muddled-an-art-history-mystery-180988677/</guid></item><item><title>癌症在心脏中是罕见的。一项小鼠研究发现，该器官的节律性节拍可能会阻止疾病的发生</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/cancer-is-somehow-rare-in-the-heart-turns-out-the-organs-rhythmic-beat-might-keep-the-disease-at-bay-a-mouse-study-finds-180988666/</link><description>不到百分之一的癌症是从心脏开始的，而从其他地方开始的疾病很少会扩散到泵血器官。新研究表明机械力可能具有保护作用</description><pubDate>Tue, 05 May 2026 18:31:13 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/cancer-is-somehow-rare-in-the-heart-turns-out-the-organs-rhythmic-beat-might-keep-the-disease-at-bay-a-mouse-study-finds-180988666/</guid></item><item><title>在古代世界，这种颜料比黄金更有价值。考古学家发现它与婴儿一起埋在罗马棺材里</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/in-the-ancient-world-this-pigment-was-worth-more-than-gold-archaeologists-discovered-it-buried-with-babies-in-roman-coffins-180988678/</link><description>罗马约克郡的葬礼习俗是在埋葬前将液体石膏浇在尸体上，保留了提尔紫色的痕迹</description><pubDate>Tue, 05 May 2026 18:20:42 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/in-the-ancient-world-this-pigment-was-worth-more-than-gold-archaeologists-discovered-it-buried-with-babies-in-roman-coffins-180988678/</guid></item><item><title>有人告诉你要“感冒时吃点东西”。一项新研究表明，饮食确实可以增强您的免疫系统细胞</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/youve-been-told-to-feed-a-cold-turns-out-eating-may-truly-boost-your-immune-system-cells-according-to-a-new-study-180988673/</link><description>针对感染和疾病的 T 细胞在餐后会变得更加有效。这一发现可能有助于改善抗癌疗法并优化我们对疫苗的反应</description><pubDate>Tue, 05 May 2026 15:56:39 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/youve-been-told-to-feed-a-cold-turns-out-eating-may-truly-boost-your-immune-system-cells-according-to-a-new-study-180988673/</guid></item><item><title>冥王星能再次被视为行星吗？美国宇航局局长的新言论凸显了科学家之间的持久争论</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/coul